Lab 7: Cluster and node maintenance with CronJobs

Objective
Use a CronJob to automate periodic work.

Good example
A simple cleanup or logging task.

Step 1: Create a project
oc new-project cron-demo

Step 2: Create a CronJob
Create cronjob.yaml

apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: hello-cron
spec:
  schedule: "*/2 * * * *"
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: hello
            image: registry.access.redhat.com/ubi9/ubi-minimal
            command:
            - /bin/sh
            - -c
            - date; echo "OpenShift CronJob executed"
          restartPolicy: OnFailure

Apply it:
oc apply -f cronjob.yaml

Step 3: Check CronJob
oc get cronjob

Step 4: Wait a couple of minutes and check Jobs
oc get jobs

Step 5: View pod logs from the job
oc get pods
oc logs <job-pod-name>

CronJobs are used for:
backups
cleanup
periodic reports
maintenance tasks

Diagram
    Cron schedule
        ↓
    CronJob creates Job
        ↓
    Job creates Pod
        ↓
    Pod runs task and exits

